sql:
SELECT al.access_date
FROM access_logs al
WHERE al.access_type = 'view';

SELECT COUNT(name) 
FROM official_trade_names 
WHERE regulated_by = 'FAO';

SELECT s.species, ot.name 
FROM species s
JOIN official_trade_names ot ON s.species_id = ot.species_id;

SELECT name
FROM common_names
WHERE species_id = 0 AND dialect = 'Malay';

SELECT s.species_id, s.scientific_name, cn.name AS common_name
FROM species s
LEFT JOIN common_names cn ON s.species_id = cn.species_id;

external_knowledge:
- The term "overview" implies gathering a broad range of information about each species;
- "Common names in different regions" indicates that the common name may vary based on the region;
- "Synonyms" refers to alternative names used for the species;
- "Who initially described them" means identifying the scientist who first provided a description of the species, recorded under the 'authority' field;
- The "year" refers to the year the species was first scientifically described, found in the 'year_described' field.
